      • getLengthSubclassType

        public static Length getLengthSubclassType(double value,
                           java.lang.String unit)
        Method to evaluate whether the supplied unit is a valid unit that can be used in the Length subclasses Meter, Yard, Foot, and Yard.
        Parameters:
        value - Value used to create the Length subclass if it is a valid unit for the subclasses of Length.
        unit - Unit will be compared against various strings to determine if it is a valid unit to be used in the creation of a subclass of Length. The following case insensitive values will match and create the mentioned subclass. 
          Meter - meter, meters, m., m
  Yard - yard, yards, yd., yd
  Inch - inch, inches, in., in
  Foot - foot, feet, ft., ft
        If values other than those defined above are supplied, null will be returned.
        Returns:
        Returns a subclass of Length (Meter, Yard, Foot, and Yard) if the unit is a valid value. Null otherwise.
